properties.name: Bay St. Louis, Mississippi
properties.description: Posted by SwinakerBay St. Louis, MississippiI traveled to Mississippi over a fall break and helped to re-build houses that were destroyed by Hurricane Katrina.

properties.name: Disney World
properties.description: Posted by SwinakerLake Buena Vista, FLMy family has vacationed in Disney World numerous times. The last time we stayed at the Grand Floridian Resort in Lake Buena Vista, FL.

properties.name: Grand Canyon
properties.description: Posted by SwinakerGrand Canyon, ArizonaThe Grand Canyon was the second stop on our trip to the West. After leaving here we headed to San Francisco. When driving there we got stuck after a car accident shut down the only interstate in \'Death Valley.\'

properties.name: Los Angeles
properties.description: Posted by SwinakerLos Angeles, CaliforniaThe only thing I liked about Los Angeles were the beaches. We were able to see Santa Monica beach and pier and Malibu Beach.

properties.name: Mont Tremblant Ski Resort
properties.description: Posted by SwinakerQuebec, CanadaMy senior year of high school I went on a ski trip with a bunch of friends to Quebec, Canada. The bus trip left Baltimore and took ten hours to get to Quebec.

properties.name: New York City
properties.description: Posted by Swinakernew york, nyI go up to New York at least three times a year whether it be with family or friends. With it being less then three hours away it makes for an easy day trip.

properties.name: Ocean City
properties.description: Posted by SwinakerOcean City, MarylandOcean City is my favorite vacation spot. I have been there every year since I was born and will continue to do so. The city has the Atlantic Ocean on one side and the Chesapeake Bay on the other side. With the peninsula being less then a mile wide you can see both bodies of water when you stand in the middle of the road.

properties.name: San Francisco
properties.description: Posted by Swinakersan francisco, caSan Francisco was my favorite stop. The public transportation made me think I was in Full House and the hills put Tennessee to shame.

properties.name: Treasure Island
properties.description: Posted by Swinaker3300 S. Las Vegas Blvd.In a trek to the West, Las Vegas was our first stop. We stayed at the Treasure Island hotel. When we left we headed to the Grand Canyon.

properties.name: University of Tennessee
properties.description: Posted by SwinakerKnoxville, TennesseeMy family made our first trip to Knoxville my junior year of high school while on a college search. Obviously it is no longer a vacation spot for me, but it is for my family and friends!
